sentence: Of these amino acids, aspartate and glutamine are used, together with carbon and nitrogen atoms from other sources, to form the purines that are used as the bases in DNA and RNA, as well as in Adenosine triphosphate, Adenosine monophosphate, Guanosine triphosphate, Nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide, Flavin adenine dinucleotide and Coenzyme A.
